    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Description\n\n[Commit 8ad2d8d](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/commit/8ad2d8d8991d868ff8e7c21a7db624f32b882531) added changes for monorepo support for JavaScript/Typescript. With this change the `root_dir` function now enforces, that the config file for eslint has to be in the same directory or below the found lock file. However it should be possible to use a config file that sits above the found lock files.\n\nIn my own setup I commented out the `stop` option of `vim.fs.find` in `root_dir` to make it work. Though that now leads to getting multiple eslint LSP instances in the same project. If I'm understanding this correctly the goal was to have only one. Shouldn't the server then use the directory of the config file as the root dir instead of the lock file?",
