        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "LSP's are also not attaching when there is no package-lock.json file nor .git directory inside the working directory. I would like to provide more data, but I am new to neovim, and don't know what that data would/should look like, or how to obtain it. There seems to be no logfile (I believe the editor doesn't identify this behavior as an error), but the command `:LspInfo` shows no lsp's attached when I open a javascript, html or css file in such a directory. In that case, wouldn't it be ok for the working directory be considered the root marker?",
